<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imbwthin" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imbwthin</refname><refpurpose>Thin a binary image.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imbwthin(image); out = imbwthin(image, method)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Binary or numeric 2D image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>method</term><listitem><para><literal>zhang-suen</literal> or <literal>guo-hall</literal>. The default is <literal>zhang-suen</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Boolean skeleton mask.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imbwthin</function> is a boolean-output compatibility entry point for <function>imthin</function>.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[mask = zeros(9, 9) == 1; mask(3:7, 5) = %t; mask(5, 3:7) = %t; out = imbwthin(mask, "guo-hall");]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imthin">imthin</link></member><member><link linkend="imbwmorph">imbwmorph</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Compatibility entry point introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
